title: PPPP Candidate Ahmed Kundi wins PK-112 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarian (PPPP) Candidate Ahmed Kundi has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-112, D.I.Khan -II by securing 33,312 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulma-e-Pakistan (JUI) candidate Sami Ullah who bagged 25,360 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 59.54 per cent.
